  "prompt": "How can a student develop the willpower to study harder than before?",
  "response": "Here are some strategies to develop stronger willpower for studying:\n\n1. Set clear, specific goals\n- Define precise academic objectives\n- Break large goals into smaller, manageable tasks\n- Create a realistic study schedule\n\n2. Develop good habits\n- Establish a consistent study routine\n- Create a dedicated study space\n- Minimize distractions (turn off notifications)\n\n3. Mental preparation\n- Practice positive self-talk\n- Visualize academic success\n- Build self-confidence\n- Understand your motivation\n\n4. Time management techniques\n- Use Pomodoro technique\n- Prioritize tasks\n- Track progress\n- Use productivity apps\n\n5. Motivation strategies\n- Reward yourself after achieving study goals\n- Find personal inspiration\n- Connect studies to long-term aspirations\n- Stay motivated by remembing your ultimate objectives\n\n6. Physical and mental wellness\n- Get adequate sleep\n- Exercise regularly\n- Maintain healthy diet\n- Practice stress management techniques\n- Meditate or practice mindfulness\n\n7. External support\n- Study with motivated peers\n- Seek guidance from teachers/mentors\n- Share goals with family/friends\n- Join study groups\n\n8. Continuous self-improvement\n- Learn from past mistakes\n- Regularly reassess and adjust strategies\n- Be patient with yourself\n\nConsistent effort and commitment are key to developing stronger willpower.",
